description.narrative:
Initial characterization of Strumica river basin is carried out;
Baseline flood risk data are collected for the needs of the Preliminary Flood  Risk Assessment;
Basin scale monitoring plan is proposed to support the characterization process;
Quantifiable reduction of agrochemicals and water used for agriculture on pilot farms;
Size of land under improved farming practices;
Hectares of land under better protection against floods with certain probability;
New management structure for long-term management of SRB
Establishment of Strumica  RBMC
Introduction of a basin-scale monitoring system;
Number of knowledge products (manuals, guidance documents, lessons learnt booklets, fact sheets and articles);

comment.narrative:
Slow progress in phased pollution reduction by industrial operations because of limited enforcement capacity 
No wastewater treatment exists in SRB at present;
Only limited technical documentation for viable wastewater management solutions for priority communities in SRB exist at present;
Current farming practice rely on an uninformed use/ overuse of agrochemicals and irrigation water;
Limited or no agricultural land currently under sustainable farming practices (e.g., GAP or agro-ecological farming);
SRB is among the country’s most vulnerable regions to the flooding hazard; significant economic losses have been encountered in the past years due to damage on agricultural land, infrastructure and other assets in Strumica River Basin;
No suitable management structure for integrated management of SRB exists at the moment;
No basin-scale monitoring system exists;
RBMC is in the process of establishment by the national authorities;
Insufficient number of knowledge products to raise awareness and promote better management practices
